# M-One Solution API — Laravel Filament CMS

## Phase 1: Package Installation
- [ ] Install Filament v3 (`filament/filament`)
- [ ] Install Spatie Media Library (`spatie/laravel-medialibrary`) + image optimization
- [ ] Install Spatie Laravel Permission (`spatie/laravel-permission`)
- [ ] Install Laravel Sanctum (for API token auth, already included in L12)
- [ ] Install `fruitcake/laravel-cors` or use built-in Laravel CORS

## Phase 2: Core Setup
- [ ] Configure [.env](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/.env) (App name, DB, Cache, etc.)
- [ ] Configure `config/cors.php` — whitelist Next.js domain
- [ ] Create Filament admin panel user seeder (Super Admin)
- [ ] Add Spatie Permission roles: `super_admin`, `editor`

## Phase 3: Models & Migrations
- [ ] `categories` migration + Model (for post categories)
- [ ] `posts` (Blog) migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `services` migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `projects` (Portfolio) migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `team_members` migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `alumnis` migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `testimonials` migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `partners` migration + Model + Media relationship
- [ ] `settings` (key-value store) migration + Model

## Phase 4: Filament Resources (Admin Dashboard)
- [ ] `CategoryResource` (CRUD)
- [ ] `PostResource` (Blog — Rich Editor, image upload, published_at)
- [ ] `ServiceResource` (CRUD + JSON fields for features/benefits/keywords)
- [ ] `ProjectResource` (CRUD + featured toggle)
- [ ] `TeamMemberResource` (CRUD + order_column sort)
- [ ] `AlumniResource` (CRUD + batch grouping)
- [ ] `TestimonialResource` (CRUD + active toggle + rating)
- [ ] `PartnerResource` (CRUD + logo upload)
- [ ] `SettingResource` (Key-value global settings page)
- [ ] RBAC: Lock Settings panel to `super_admin` only; editors can only access content resources

## Phase 5: REST API Endpoints
- [ ] Create `api.php` routes file
- [ ] `GET /api/posts` — list published posts (paginated)
- [ ] `GET /api/posts/{slug}` — single post
- [ ] `GET /api/services` — list services
- [ ] `GET /api/services/{slug}` — single service
- [ ] `GET /api/projects` — list projects (with featured filter)
- [ ] `GET /api/team` — list team members (ordered)
- [ ] `GET /api/alumni` — list alumni (grouped by batch)
- [ ] `GET /api/testimonials` — list active testimonials
- [ ] `GET /api/partners` — list partners
- [ ] `GET /api/settings` — return all settings as key-value object

## Phase 6: API Resources & Caching
- [ ] Create API Resource classes (JSON transformation)
- [ ] Implement file-based or database caching on all GET endpoints
- [ ] Auto-clear cache on Filament save (Observer or ModelEvent)

## Phase 7: Security & Production Hardening
- [ ] Configure rate limiting (throttle middleware — 60 req/min)
- [ ] Configure CORS (only allow Next.js domain)
- [ ] Standardize JSON error responses (404, 422, 500)
- [ ] Add `Accept: application/json` middleware to ensure JSON-only responses

## Phase 8: Seeder & Testing
- [ ] DatabaseSeeder: seed dummy data for all entities
- [ ] Manual verification: Filament dashboard CRUD works
- [ ] Manual verification: API routes return correct JSON
- [ ] Run `php artisan test` to ensure no regressions
